      "rationale": "Formal model form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2. The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) is the established regulatory-accepted form for CFD hemolysis prediction in FDA submissions. Turbulence model sensitivity was evaluated as part of the validation activity and the resulting uncertainty is carried as an accepted residual within the overall credibility margin."
